abstract: For all the talk of the White House chief of staff as a moderating force, Mr. Kelly has strong feelings about patriotism and immigration that mirror those of his boss.
snippet: For all the talk of the White House chief of staff as a moderating force, Mr. Kelly has strong feelings about patriotism and immigration that mirror those of his boss.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — This past summer, the Trump administration debated lowering the annual cap on refugees admitted to the United States. Should it stay at 110,000, be cut to 50,000 or fall somewhere in between? John F. Kelly offered his opinion. If it were up to him, he said, the number would be between zero and one.

abstract: South Asians have fomented a political awakening, propelling many to get involved in campaigns and run for office.
snippet: South Asians have fomented a political awakening, propelling many to get involved in campaigns and run for office.
lead_paragraph: Upendra Chivukula had already enjoyed a string of political successes in 2014 when he decided to challenge three fellow Democrats for the New Jersey House seat that became vacant when former Representative Rush D. Holt Jr. decided not to run for re-election.

abstract: Once an informal network, a group of friends and associates is organizing a united political push on issues like education, employment and voting rights.
snippet: Once an informal network, a group of friends and associates is organizing a united political push on issues like education, employment and voting rights.
lead_paragraph: Dozens of black executives and their spouses joined Senators Cory Booker and Kamala Harris, as well as Eric H. Holder Jr., the former attorney general, for a private dinner in July in Bridgehampton, N.Y. Over kale salad and sea bass on the grounds of a hotel, the executives sought advice about their intermittent fund-raising efforts to address political and social issues, and for the candidates who support those causes.

headline_main: California Today: Talking to a Democratic Challenger for Feinstein

abstract: The moves came as employees and business partners of the company voiced concern about sexual harassment allegations, revealed in a New York Times investigation.
snippet: The moves came as employees and business partners of the company voiced concern about sexual harassment allegations, revealed in a New York Times investigation.
lead_paragraph: The Weinstein Company struggled to perform damage control on Friday amid allegations of rampant sexual harassment by its co-chairman Harvey Weinstein and turmoil among its ranks. One-third of the company’s all-male board resigned, while board members who remained hired an outside law firm to investigate the allegations and announced that Mr. Weinstein would take an indefinite leave of absence immediately.

abstract: Senators Elizabeth Warren and Bernie Sanders are taking different paths to win new fans ahead of 2020. The outcome will say much about the Democrats’ future.
snippet: Senators Elizabeth Warren and Bernie Sanders are taking different paths to win new fans ahead of 2020. The outcome will say much about the Democrats’ future.
lead_paragraph: ATLANTA — It took a few minutes to find an opening, but when it came, Senator Elizabeth Warren did not squander her best chance to connect with a heavily black audience inside the Rev. Dr. Martin Luther King Jr.’s Ebenezer Baptist Church late last month.
